Etymology[edit]

Post-Classical. From fascia +‎ -ō.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ˈfas.ki.oː/, [ˈfas̠.ki.oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈfaʃ.ʃi.o/, [ˈfaʃ.ʃi.ɔ]

Verb[edit]

fasciō (present infinitive fasciāre, perfect active fasciāvī, supine fasciātum); first conjugation

  1. (rare) I envelop with bands, swathe.
